{
  "metadata": {
    "slug": "claude-liam-legal-finance",
    "title": "Claude, Counsel",
    "subtitle": "The Legal and Finance Plugins",
    "channel": "claude-liam",
    "persona": "Liam",
    "folderLabel": "@NikBearBrown",
    "audience": "Practitioners and makers following the channel's Claude workflows",
    "register": "Teardown",
    "engine": "kokoro",
    "voice": "am_onyx",
    "palette": "claude",
    "typography": { "serif": "EB Garamond", "ui": "system sans", "mono": "SF Mono" },
    "model_chip": { "model": "Fable 5", "effort": "High" },
    "source": "books/anthropics/books/claude-cowork-plugins/chapters/ch11-legal-finance.txt",
    "derived_from": "claude-cowork-plugins.md (Ch.11)",
    "genre": "deep-explainer",
    "one_idea": "Legal and finance are the two 'essentials' that protect a small operator — legal flags the concerning clause before you sign, finance models the scenario before you commit — but both only screen and accelerate; the consequential call stays with a human, and for real stakes, a real lawyer or CFO.",
    "duration_estimate_s": 300,
    "lane_histogram_target": { "VOX": "20-25%", "MANIM": "25-40%", "REMOTION": "30-45%", "CARD": "remainder" }
  },
  "beats": [
    {
      "id": "B00", "act": "COLD OPEN", "lane": "ASK", "scene": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
      "greeting": "Shalom, Liam",
      "props": { "command": "Which two plugins actually protect a one-person business?", "runningText": "thinking…", "output": ["Legal — it flags the clause before you sign.", "Finance — it models the scenario before you commit."] },
      "narration_text": "Shalom — this is Liam, in for Bear. Two plugins do the unglamorous work that keeps a small operation out of trouble: legal reads a contract before you sign it, finance runs the numbers before you commit. Here's what each one screens for — and exactly where each one stops.",
      "spark_line": "Screen before you sign."
    },

    { "id": "C01", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "The Shared Pattern" }, "narration_text": "Start with what these two have in common.", "spark_line": "The Shared Pattern" },
    {
      "id": "B01", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "PredictCard",
      "narration_text": "Most independent operators sign contracts without reading them closely, and track their finances without ever analyzing them. Not because they're careless — because they're busy, and both of these feel like specialist work.",
      "show": "A single figure carrying two heavy folders — 'contracts' and 'finances' — neither one opened.",
      "spark_line": "Busy, not careless."
    },
    {
      "id": "B02", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B02.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.5] },
      "narration_text": "So the NDA gets signed unread. The vendor terms get accepted because pushing back feels awkward. The receipts pile up in a folder nobody analyzes. This is the gap both plugins are built for.",
      "show": "A still of a person signing a stack of paperwork in a hurry; slow push-in.",
      "spark_line": "The unread stack.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a person at a desk signing a stack of paperwork in a hurry, receipts nearby; documentary duotone. No real logos, no identifiable person, no real party names."
    },
    {
      "id": "B03", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ChipGrid",
      "narration_text": "And they share one shape. Neither plugin makes you a professional. Each one gives you a structured first pass — it screens the risk, or accelerates the analysis — and tells you when to bring in a human.",
      "show": "Two chips resolve onto the stage: Screen the risk · Accelerate the analysis.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "ChipGrid", "chips": ["Screen the risk", "Accelerate the analysis"] },
      "spark_line": "Screen and accelerate."
    },
    {
      "id": "B04", "act": "ACT I", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/coverage_net_firstpass.mp4",
      "narration_text": "Structured first-pass coverage. It won't catch everything a specialist would — but it catches what you'd otherwise miss entirely, because the honest alternative wasn't a careful review. The alternative was no review at all.",
      "show": "Items rain down; a net catches the ones that matter while a few slip past — beside it, an empty net catches nothing.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "filter", "in": "everything you sign and spend", "caught": "what you'd have missed", "against": "no review at all" },
      "spark_line": "Better than no review."
    },

    { "id": "C02", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "The Legal Plugin" }, "narration_text": "First, the one that reads your contracts.", "spark_line": "The Legal Plugin" },
    {
      "id": "B05", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B05.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "drawon", "focus": [0.5, 0.45] },
      "narration_text": "The legal plugin is a screening tool. It reads a document against established risk frameworks and flags what deserves your attention — the one clause on the page that could cost you later.",
      "show": "A still of a contract page; a terracotta highlight draws on around a single clause.",
      "spark_line": "A screening tool.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a generic contract page with one clause; terracotta highlight added at previz. No real party names, no logos."
    },
    {
      "id": "B06", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "code-block",
      "narration_text": "In practice, you upload a contract and ask plainly: review this agreement and flag any issues — what should I worry about? No legal vocabulary required. Claude reads the whole thing and answers.",
      "show": "Onda code-block: a composer line typing the review request.",
      "props": { "code": "Review this agreement and flag any issues.\nWhat should I worry about?" },
      "spark_line": "Flag any issues."
    },
    {
      "id": "B07", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/legal_flag_counts.mp4",
      "narration_text": "What comes back is a risk summary with color-coded flags. Green for standard terms, yellow for items worth a second look, red for real concerns. Each flag explained — what the clause says, why it's flagged, and what you might do about it.",
      "show": "Flags sort into three columns by color — green, yellow, red — the tallies settling as illustrative, not a fixed output.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "state", "buckets": ["green: standard", "yellow: attention", "red: concern"], "note": "counts illustrative, never a fixed number" },
      "spark_line": "Green, yellow, red."
    },
    {
      "id": "B08", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ChipGrid",
      "narration_text": "The screening covers the routine documents a solo operator actually faces: contract review, NDA triage, vendor-agreement analysis, compliance checks — and for yellow or red items, suggested redline language if you decide to negotiate.",
      "show": "Five chips resolve: Contract review · NDA triage · Vendor terms · Compliance checks · Redline language.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "ChipGrid", "chips": ["Contract review", "NDA triage", "Vendor terms", "Compliance checks", "Redline language"] },
      "spark_line": "What it screens."
    },
    {
      "id": "B09", "act": "ACT II", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/threshold_hours_to_minutes.mp4",
      "narration_text": "And it changes the economics of review. Thorough reading drops from hours to minutes — which is the whole point. It makes contract review a default step, not the exception you skip when you're signing in a hurry.",
      "show": "A long 'hours' bar collapses past a threshold into a short 'minutes' bar; 'default, not exception' lands.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "threshold", "before": "hours", "after": "minutes", "unlocks": "review as a default step" },
      "spark_line": "Review as default."
    },

    { "id": "C03", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "Not a Lawyer" }, "narration_text": "Now the line you can't cross.", "spark_line": "Not a Lawyer" },
    {
      "id": "B10", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ChipGrid",
      "narration_text": "Because here's what it does not do. It doesn't give legal advice. It doesn't weigh a clause against the strategy of your business. It doesn't replace qualified counsel for significant matters. And it doesn't guarantee its read is legally sound. Take all four seriously.",
      "show": "Four caution chips resolve: No legal advice · No strategic weighing · No counsel for big deals · No legal guarantee.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "ChipGrid", "chips": ["No legal advice", "No strategic weighing", "No counsel for big deals", "No legal guarantee"] },
      "spark_line": "Four hard limits."
    },
    {
      "id": "B11", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B11.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.4, 0.5], "vox_run": "R1",
        "handoff": { "camera": { "x": 0.4, "y": 0.5, "scale": 1.6 }, "objects": [ { "id": "flag", "x": 0.42, "y": 0.48, "scale": 1.0, "opacity": 1 } ] } },
      "narration_text": "It's the difference between a screen that catches the obvious problem sitting on the page…",
      "show": "A still of a contract under a magnifier, one clause flagged; slow push toward the flag.",
      "spark_line": "The screen catches.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a contract under a magnifier with one flagged clause; duotone. Continuity start of vox_run R1. No real party names."
    },
    {
      "id": "B12", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B12.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.62, 0.5], "vox_run": "R1",
        "handoff": { "camera": { "x": 0.62, "y": 0.5, "scale": 1.8 }, "objects": [ { "id": "counsel", "x": 0.6, "y": 0.48, "scale": 1.0, "opacity": 1 } ] } },
      "narration_text": "…and outside counsel who tells you whether to sign. For routine work — the NDA, the SaaS terms, the freelancer agreement you reuse — screening beats no review at all. For high-stakes deals, call a lawyer. The plugin helps you know which one you're in.",
      "show": "Continuous move to a second desk — a professional marking up the contract; same room grammar as B11.",
      "spark_line": "Counsel makes the call.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a professional at a desk marking up a contract — 'counsel'; same duotone and room grammar as B11 (vox_run R1). No identifiable person."
    },
    {
      "id": "B13", "act": "ACT III", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/branch_routine_vs_highstakes.mp4",
      "narration_text": "That's the real skill it hands you: triage. Routine and low-stakes, the screen is enough. Complex, or high-stakes, and a red flag is your signal to escalate — to a person, before you sign.",
      "show": "One contract enters a fork: 'routine' flows down to the screen; 'high-stakes' routes up to a human.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "branch", "in": "a contract", "low": "screen it", "high": "escalate to a lawyer" },
      "spark_line": "Know which you're in."
    },

    { "id": "C04", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "The Finance Plugin" }, "narration_text": "Now the one that reads your numbers.", "spark_line": "The Finance Plugin" },
    {
      "id": "B14", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B14.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.5] },
      "narration_text": "The finance plugin brings financial analysis into Claude. Its real value isn't the deep dive — it's turning analysis into something you actually do, instead of something you keep meaning to do.",
      "show": "A still of a solo operator at night over a laptop and printed statements; slow push-in.",
      "spark_line": "Do it, don't mean to.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a solo operator at night over a laptop and printed financial statements; duotone. No identifiable person, no real figures."
    },
    {
      "id": "B15", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "code-block",
      "narration_text": "You point Claude at your data and ask the questions you've been putting off. Here's six months of revenue and expenses — what's my burn rate, and how long is my runway at this pace?",
      "show": "Onda code-block: a composer line typing the finance question.",
      "props": { "code": "Here's 6 months of revenue and expenses.\nWhat's my burn rate and runway?" },
      "spark_line": "Point it at your data."
    },
    {
      "id": "B16", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ChipGrid",
      "narration_text": "From there it does the kind of analysis a fractional CFO would: budget and variance tracking, revenue forecasting, expense trends, simple modeling, and clean reports — for you, or for a lender or investor.",
      "show": "Five chips resolve: Budget & variance · Forecasting · Expense trends · Modeling · Reports.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "ChipGrid", "chips": ["Budget & variance", "Forecasting", "Expense trends", "Modeling", "Reports"] },
      "spark_line": "What it analyzes."
    },
    {
      "id": "B17", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/runway_burn_depletion.mp4",
      "narration_text": "The health check first: your monthly burn rate, and your runway — how many months the cash lasts at the current pace. The number you keep avoiding, made plain in seconds.",
      "show": "A cash bar drains month by month toward zero; the runway length reads out as it empties.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "depletion", "metric": "runway (months of cash)", "driver": "monthly burn rate" },
      "spark_line": "Burn and runway."
    },
    {
      "id": "B18", "act": "ACT IV", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/scenario_model_payback.mp4",
      "narration_text": "Then the part that earns its keep: scenario modeling. Raise prices by, say, fifteen percent — where's the break-even? Hire a contractor who helps you land more clients — how long until the hire pays for itself? Claude models best, likely, and worst case, shows the math, and you adjust the assumptions and rerun.",
      "show": "Three payback curves — best, likely, worst — climb toward a break-even line at different speeds.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "scenario", "lines": ["best case", "likely case", "worst case"], "target": "break-even / payback", "note": "the 15% and the hire are illustrative assumptions, not fixed facts" },
      "spark_line": "Best, likely, worst."
    },

    { "id": "C05", "act": "ACT V", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "Not a CFO" }, "narration_text": "And the line on this side.", "spark_line": "Not a CFO" },
    {
      "id": "B19", "act": "ACT V", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ChipGrid",
      "narration_text": "The limits, just as plainly. It won't file your taxes. It won't give you accounting advice. It won't replace a bookkeeper for complex records. And it won't guarantee its numbers are accurate for a regulator.",
      "show": "Four caution chips resolve: Won't file taxes · No accounting advice · No bookkeeping · No regulatory guarantee.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "ChipGrid", "chips": ["Won't file taxes", "No accounting advice", "No bookkeeping", "No regulatory guarantee"] },
      "spark_line": "Four hard limits."
    },
    {
      "id": "B20", "act": "ACT V", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B20.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "drawon", "focus": [0.5, 0.45] },
      "narration_text": "It builds the model — but it can't tell you the assumptions fit your industry, or that the figure will hold up to the taxman. The math is fast; the judgment is yours.",
      "show": "A still of a person paused over a hiring decision and a spreadsheet; a terracotta ring draws on around the person.",
      "spark_line": "The judgment is yours.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: a person pausing over a decision at a desk with a spreadsheet; terracotta ring added at previz. No identifiable person, no real figures."
    },
    {
      "id": "B21", "act": "ACT V", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/branch_analysis_to_human.mp4",
      "narration_text": "So the finance plugin gives you the analysis a CFO would produce — but the consequential call stays with a human, and for real stakes, a real accountant signs off. An accelerator, not a CFO.",
      "show": "A finished model flows toward a decision point where a human — not the plugin — makes the call.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "branch", "in": "the finished model", "out": "human decision", "note": "real stakes route to a real accountant" },
      "spark_line": "The call stays human."
    },

    { "id": "C06", "act": "ACT VI", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "SegmentCard", "props": { "title": "Make It Routine" }, "narration_text": "Last — how to actually get the value.", "spark_line": "Make It Routine" },
    {
      "id": "B22", "act": "ACT VI", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "illustration/three-habits-triptych",
      "narration_text": "Three habits make both worth it. Run them routinely, not occasionally — the value is in the habit. Treat every red flag as a signal to escalate. And keep your documents organized, so Claude can actually find them.",
      "show": "Three panels light in turn: Routine, not occasional · Escalate the red flags · Organized documents.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "triptych", "panels": ["Routine, not occasional", "Escalate the red flags", "Organized documents"] },
      "spark_line": "Three habits."
    },
    {
      "id": "B23", "act": "ACT VI", "lane": "MANIM", "scene": "manim/cost_rises_the_later.mp4",
      "narration_text": "Because the value isn't the one-off deep dive — it's catching problems early. A bad clause, a financial trend that doesn't add up: the cost of fixing it climbs the longer it hides. Monthly reviews and automatic screening catch it while it's still cheap.",
      "show": "A cost curve rises steeply over time; an early catch sits low on the curve, a late catch far up it.",
      "viz": { "pattern": "growth", "x": "time until caught", "y": "cost to fix", "mark": "catch early = cheapest" },
      "spark_line": "Early is cheapest."
    },
    {
      "id": "B24", "act": "ACT VI", "lane": "VOX", "scene": "media/B24.png",
      "shot": { "type": "STILL", "source": "ai", "motion": "kenburns", "focus": [0.5, 0.5] },
      "narration_text": "And the simplest lever of all: a folder of contracts, a folder of financial records, consistently kept. The more easily Claude can find them, the more useful both plugins become.",
      "show": "A still of two neatly labeled folders — contracts and finances — on a tidy desk; slow push-in.",
      "spark_line": "Keep it findable.",
      "pantry_note": "Tier 1 illustrative: two neatly labeled folders — contracts and finances — on a tidy desk; duotone. Generic labels, no real names or logos."
    },

    {
      "id": "V01", "act": "CLOSE", "lane": "REMOTION", "scene": "ClaudeVerdictArtifact",
      "lead_silence_s": 0.5,
      "narration_text": "Let's recap with Claude. These are the two essentials for a small operation. The legal plugin is a screening tool: it reads a contract against risk frameworks and flags what deserves your attention — green, yellow, red — before you sign. The finance plugin is an analysis accelerator: it models burn rate, runway, and the what-if before you commit. Both screen and accelerate; neither one is the lawyer or the CFO. Run them routinely, and when a red flag surfaces, that's your signal to call a professional.",
      "props": { "artifactLines": [ "Two separate plugins, one job: protect the solo operator", "Legal screens the contract — green, yellow, red — before you sign", "Finance models the scenario — burn, runway, what-if — before you commit", "Both screen and accelerate; neither is the professional", "Routine, not occasional — escalate red flags to a real lawyer or CFO" ] },
      "spark_line": "The verdict."
    },
    {
      "id": "H01", "act": "CLOSE", "lane": "ASK", "scene": "ClaudeComposerAsk",
      "greeting": "Your turn.",
      "props": { "command": "I run a one-person business. I'm about to sign a vendor contract and set next quarter's budget. Act as my first-pass screen, not my lawyer or my CFO: (1) tell me exactly what to paste in so the legal plugin can flag the concerning clauses, (2) show me the three scenarios the finance plugin should model before I commit to a new hire, and (3) for each, name the exact moment I should stop and call a real lawyer or accountant.", "runningText": "paste this into Claude…" },
      "narration_text": "Your turn. Paste this into Claude: I run a one-person business, and I'm about to sign a vendor contract and set next quarter's budget. Act as my first-pass screen, not my lawyer or my CFO — tell me what to paste in so the legal plugin can flag the concerning clauses, show me the three scenarios the finance plugin should model before I commit to a new hire, and for each, name the exact moment I should stop and call a real lawyer or accountant. It turns this chapter into a screen for your own next decision — run it, and watch where it tells you to escalate.",
      "spark_line": "Screen it, model it."
    },
    {
      "id": "O01", "act": "CLOSE", "lane": "CARD", "scene": "ClaudeTitleOutro",
      "narration_text": "Claude, Counsel.",
      "props": { "title": "Claude, Counsel", "handle": "@NikBearBrown", "subline": "The Legal and Finance plugins" },
      "spark_line": "Claude, Counsel"
    }
  ]
}
